## Classe `RequestMediaDTO`

C’est l’objet reçu dans le `POST`.

```java
package com.example.demo.media;

import jakarta.validation.constraints.Max;
import jakarta.validation.constraints.Min;
import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotBlank;
import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;

public class RequestMediaDTO {

    @NotBlank(message = "title est obligatoire")
    private String title;

    @NotBlank(message = "type est obligatoire")
    private String type;

    @NotNull(message = "year est obligatoire")
    @Min(value = 1900, message = "year doit etre superieur ou egal a 1900")
    @Max(value = 2100, message = "year doit etre inferieur ou egal a 2100")
    private Integer year;

    public String getTitle() {
        return title;
    }

    public void setTitle(String title) {
        this.title = title;
    }

    public String getType() {
        return type;
    }

    public void setType(String type) {
        this.type = type;
    }

    public Integer getYear() {
        return year;
    }

    public void setYear(Integer year) {
        this.year = year;
    }
}
```

